cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with wireless network deployment and pricing strategies. 
- cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics) is also likely as the paper studies the optimal pricing and bandwidth allocation strategies in both monopoly and competitive scenarios. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the impact of bandwidth regulations on small-cell deployment. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is possible as the paper mentions providing service to mobile and fixed users. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper may touch on security concerns related to small-cell deployment.
